e, SDK and API for third party websites and applications.<br/><br/>This Privacy Policy explains:<br/><br/>the type of personal data we collect and how we collect it<br/>how we use your personal data<br/>the parties that we disclose the personal data to; and<br/>the choices we offer, including how to access and update your personal data.<br/><br/>Information We may Collect from You<br/><br/>YubeFit receives or collects information when we operate and provide our Services, including when you install, access or use our Services.<br/><br/>Personal Data We May Collect from You<br/><br/>We may collect the following personal data from you:<br/><br/>personal information to establish your identity and background such as your full name, passport or identity card number, photo and nationality<br/>contact information such mobile phone number and email address<br/>geographic location information: including precise geographic location information obtained by GPS information, WLAN access point, Bluetooth, base station and other sensor information, and approximate geographic location information obtained by network location information (such as base station, IP and WLAN)<br/>address book from mobile phone number and email address, camera, microphone, photo and storage of data files including but not limited text, pdf, audio, image and video<br/>payment information such as your bank account number, bank account holder full name and details, bank swift code and other bank account details<br/>recording of your photograph during any of our corporate events or third-party open day<br/>recording of calls placed by you to our customer services<br/>function or post when you commence a business relationship with us<br/>resume or CVs when you apply job with us<br/><br/>For general browsing although no personal data is revealed to us, certain technical and statistical information is available to us via our internet service provider such as cookies, your IP address, the time, date and duration